Feature: bootstrap of a lead shop installs the lead's BC CLIs from VCS/published packages, not editable-from-clone, so the lead host carries no "repos/" BC source

  Supersedes scenario 67 (features/templates/67-lead-bootstrap-installs-sibling-bc-clones-editable-into-product-venv.gherkin). The Implementer must locate the BC-side hash of scenario 67 in the shopsystem-templates feature surface and retire that hash when landing this scenario. Scheduling note (ADR-018): this re-grounding rides the same request_bugfix as scenarios 124–128 but is gated behind the "repos/" migration ADR-018 names as a downstream consequence (switch the lead's BC-CLI installs from editable-from-clone to VCS/published, then land this scenario).

  Scenario 67 pinned that the lead-shop bootstrap installs each sibling BC clone under "repos/" into the product venv in editable mode, so the lead's CLIs resolve to local clone source. ADR-018 (pinning PDR-011) names that editable-from-clone install as the actual lead-tooling coupling that keeps a "repos/" directory physically present on the lead host — the one thing that contradicts the lead-out-of-code doctrine (D1). The end state ADR-018 names: the bootstrap installs the lead's BC CLIs from VCS or published packages, not editable-from-clone. This end state is already the realized pattern for the "scenarios" distribution, which is installed from a VCS pin ("github.com/dstengle/shopsystem-scenarios" at "v0.1.0") rather than editable from "repos/shopsystem-scenarios". Switching the BC-CLI installs to that pattern is what dissolves the lead host's "repos/" dependency. This scenario re-grounds the pin from editable-from-clone to VCS/published install.

  @scenario_hash:7568d14e0a13eca4
  Scenario: bootstrap of a lead shop installs the "shop-msg" BC CLI into the product venv from a VCS/published package pin, with no editable install resolving into a "repos/" clone
    Given a target directory "/tmp/example-lead-shop" containing an existing git repository
    And the bootstrap configuration pins the lead's "shop-msg" BC CLI to a VCS/published package source (in the shape of the existing "scenarios" pin "github.com/dstengle/shopsystem-scenarios" at "v0.1.0"), with no "repos/" clone present at the target
    When I invoke the "shop-templates" bootstrap entry point with shop type "lead", shop name "shopsystem-product", and target directory "/tmp/example-lead-shop"
    Then the exit code is 0
    And the "pip show shop-msg" output for the product venv records the install as not editable
    And the product venv reports the installed location of the "shop-msg" distribution as resolving to a site-packages path, not into any "repos/" directory of the target
    And the "shop-msg" distribution's recorded install origin is a VCS/published-package URL, not a local "repos/" directory path
    And the target directory contains no "repos/" directory after the bootstrap completes
